This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories, as it deals with automating the process of neural architecture design and improving the performance of the DARTS method on benchmark datasets. It also involves optimization techniques and the use of hyper-networks, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the computer architecture (cs.AR) sub-category, as it deals with designing efficient and effective neural network architectures.
